The paper focuses on using deep learning methods, specifically convolutional networks, for automatic organ segmentation in medical imaging. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of large annotated training sets and parallel computing resources is mentioned, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also specifically mentions the segmentation of the pancreas in CT imaging, which falls under the medical imaging (cs.MED) sub-category. Finally, the use of probability response maps and random forest classifiers suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR).
